                            Installation instruction
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. FreeBSD
~~~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (tbz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

b. From source package

   Build and install:
   # tar -xzf chc-0.2.tar.gz
   # ./configure
   # make
   # make install

   Remove:
   # make uninstall

2. Linux
~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (deb, rpm, txz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

a. From binary (tgz) package



b. From source package
















- use 






    # cp chc-0.1-i586.tar.gz /opt
    # cd /opt
    # tar -xzf chc-0.1-i586.tar.gz
    # cd chc
    # ./create_links

                or

    # tar -xzf chc-0.1-i586.tar.gz
    # cd chc
    # ./install

b. Installation from '.bin' package

    # ./chc-0.1-i586.bin

c. Installation from source package
     
    # tar -xzf chc-0.1.tar.gz
    # ./configure
    # make
    # make install

2. Uninstall
------------

a. If you installed it from binary '.tar.gz' package

    # /opt/chc/remove_links
    # rm -r /opt/chc/

            or

    # /opt/chc/uninstall

b. If you installed it from '.bin' package

    # /opt/chc/uninstall

c. If you installed it from source package:

    # make uninstall

